==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tussah silk
<hw>Tus"sah silk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Probably fr. Hind.
<ets>tasar</ets> a shuttle, Skr. <ets>tasara</ets>,
<ets>trasara</ets>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A silk cloth made from the
cocoons of a caterpillar other than the common silkworm, much used in
Bengal and China.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The silk fiber itself.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>tusseh silk</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tussal</ent>⟦br⟧
